{"build_type":"library","description":"As-completed per-item worker: receives one work item JSON {path} giving a binary's full path, splits it at the final slash into directory + name, loads that binary and its relocation closure by name from the directory via the no-fork native loader (resolve-closure-towards-invoking-entry-point) and runs it, then returns a non-zero {launched:1} completion marker. A worker that returns reports completion; a perpetual worker (the supervisor) never returns, so the collector stays alive on it. ITEM ARG IS NOW A CSTRING (flat bytes from the queue, A2): decode it to a node first, then read fields.","module_name":"load-and-invoke-binary-from-received-path","package_name":"load-and-invoke-binary-from-received-path","function_definitions":{"load-and-invoke-binary-from-received-path":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"item","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"c24","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":24},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"k_path","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"path"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"argjson","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"{}"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"k_launched","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"launched"},{"instruction_type":"function_invocation","invocation